# 3. 離れ離れになること

Shiho: So, Minori, you're thinking about switching to the credit-based course?
Minori: Y-Yeah... But I haven't made my final decision yet...
Kohane: Right... You and your group have become famous enough to start appearing on TV and radio programs together.
Shiho: True. I remember hearing from Shizuku when she first enrolled that this school's credit-based course gives her more flexibility to work...
Shiho: So, I think it's a good idea. I mean, you want to keep pursuing your dream, right?
Minori: Shiho...
Kohane: But it is a little sad to hear that...
Minori: What...?
Kohane: No, it's just... I know you worked really hard to become an idol, and are still working hard...
Kohane: So if this makes things easier for you... If you think this is the right way to go, Minori, I want to give you my support...
Kohane: But it also means seeing less of each other at school, and there'd be no chance of us being in the same class again.
Minori: Oh...
Minori: That was actually kinda bothering me too...
Minori: Airi's currently credit-based, and Haruka was before... And they both said it was sad they didn't get to see their friends as much after switching...
Shiho: I mean, it seems only natural not being able to see your friends as much since you're going to physically be at school less.
Shiho: I'm not sure there's much you can do about that.
Minori: R...
Minori: Right...
Shiho: At the same time, what do I know? In the end, Minori, you have to make your own decision...
Shiho: Still, if I were in your position, I'd probably choose the credit-based course.
Minori: What...?
Shiho: Yes, I wouldn't be able to see my friends as much, but we don't necessarily have to talk at school and stuff.
Shiho: I may be busy working, but we could always set aside time to meet or hang out.
Shiho: And if going credit-based made it easier for me to make my dream come true, then I'd absolutely choose that option.
Kohane: I agree...
Minori: You do?
Kohane: Oh, um... I know I said that I'd be sad...
Kohane: But placing myself in your shoes, Minori... I'd also probably want to switch if it was the best way to make my dream come true...
Minori: Kohane...
Kohane: We might not be able to have lunch together or talk like this as much...
Kohane: But your dream is to spread hope to as many people as you can as an idol... I really want that to happen.
Minori: Oh...
Minori: Thank you both. I'm really glad I talked to you about this...
Minori: I feel like I got some courage!
Shiho: That's good to hear.
Minori: And if I do end up switching to the credit-based course, I promise to still message you guys. Every single day...
Minori: No, every single hour!
Shiho: Yeah, that seems like a bit much.
Minori: Whaaat?!
Minori: Heh heh heh...
Minori: I ended up making some Print Stickers with Shiho and Kohane♪
Minori: Hehe. I'll keep them in my phone case!
Minori: And I couldn't be happier... They said they'll support my decision, and that we'll be friends forever...
Minori: I feel the same way... I won't get to see them at school as much, but I still wanna keep being friends.
Minori: So, I'm sure it'll be okay... As long as we feel that way about each other, we're not going to end up completely separated.
Minori: Alright...
Minori: That just leaves schoolwork.
Minori: Going credit-based means having to plan ahead and learn what I can from my textbooks. Plus, I won't really have time to ask my teachers any questions...
Minori: How am I gonna handle all that...?
Minori: No, I can't let that get to me now.
Minori: I have to figure out a way.
Minori: Mom! Dad! There's something I need to discuss with you guys.
